records.addlTxt:
Defendant in custody on WRIT.
NO CONTEST plea entered to counts 1 and 2, two counts felony bail jumping.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in count 3. Motion granted.
Sentence is withheld and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two (2) years, consecutive to the prison sentence presently being served on 15 CF 261, to commence upon defendant's discharge date after extended supervision ends.  Court authorizes transfer to probation to the State of Iowa if DOC approves.
Conditions of probation:
1) Pay court costs;
2) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
3) provide DNA sample;
4) maintain fulltime employment or work search;
5) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
6) AODA assessment and follow through;
7) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same, if deemed appropriate by the agent.
Minutes.
